nd opened the first Institute of Sexology in Berlin after the First World War.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 4aBiografie. 4aJudenverfolgung. 4aMedizingeschichte. 4aPersecution of the Jews. 4aSchwulenbewegung. 4aSexualwissenschaft. 4abiography. 4agay liberation. 4ahistory of medicine. 4asexology. 7aMEDICAL / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2017z9783110547764oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831105480060 cprintz978311054769640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110548426423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110548426.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEGb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017